🔥 Production Scenario
Problem

A company's operations team manually checks 50 Linux servers every morning.

Each server requires checking:

CPU usage
Memory usage
Disk usage
Running services
Uptime
Your Task

Write a Bash script that:

Reads server names from servers.txt.
Connects using SSH.
Runs the required checks.
Saves reports to reports/<hostname>.txt.
Logs failures to logs/failed_servers.log.
Continues even if one server is offline.
🧠 Senior DevOps Challenge

